  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Eligible were all children aged three to eight years with a normal psychophysical
             development, and onset of esotropia before age one who visited one of the clinics
             during the study period.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  previous strabismus surgery, an angle of strabismus larger than 24° or smaller than
             10°, any normal binocular vision, convergence excess with angle of strabismus at near
             fixation 1.5 times larger than the angle at distance, more than 1 line Logmar acuity
             difference between the two eyes, hypermetropia over 6 diopters or myopia over 3
             diopters, up- or downshoot in (25°) adduction more than 8°, V-pattern (25° up and down
             gaze) over 8°, A-pattern (25° up and down gaze) over 5° and manifest vertical
             strabismus over 4°
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
    <gender>All</gender>
    <minimum_age>3 Years</minimum_age>
    <maximum_age>8 Years</maximum_age>
